{"key":"processedPost-9167444","value":{"id":9167444,"first":9166981,"last":9168254,"when":1225553520,"utime":"11/01/08 06:32 PM","content":"Agreed.&nbsp; Personally, I'd fruit it uncased.&nbsp; By casing, you might get slightly larger fruits, but with good environmental controls such as 99% humidity, bright high frequency light in the 5,000K to 6,500K range, several light mistings per day, and lots of fresh air, you can get a great pinset uncased, and it comes a week or two sooner.&nbsp;  <br /><br />In addition, casing materials, since they're uncolonized and exposed, are prone to molds, while fully colonized substrates are quite resistant.<br />RR","title":"Re: Bulk Substrate"}}